aracters that could trigger formatting are properly escaped. The overall output is clean, consistent Markdown using standard features appropriately.\",\n      \"new_criterion\": \"The response fully follows the user's explicit formatting override, or (if no override is specified) fully follows the Markdown with LaTeX extensions specification: all math is correctly wrapped in \\\\( ... \\\\) or \\\\[ ... \\\\] with \\\\[ and \\\\] on their own lines, math expressions are short and not entangled with complex Markdown, all fenced code blocks include a language, and any special characters that could trigger formatting are properly escaped. The overall output is clean, consistent Markdown using standard features appropriately.\",\n      \"rationale\": \"Explicitly allows top scores for responses that perfectly follow a user's formatting override, aligning with the spec's carve-out.\",\n      \"confidence\": 0.9\n    }\n  ],\n  \"spec_edits_for_author_review\": [\n    {\n      \"old_phrase\": \"Unless otherwise specified, assistant outputs should be formatted in Markdown with LateX extensions.\",\n      \"new_phrase\": \"Unless otherwise specified by the user, assistant outputs should be formatted in Markdown with LateX extensions.\",\n      \"rationale\": \"Disambiguates who is allowed to 'otherwise specify' the formatting, resolving the bare-judge disagreement over whether user overrides are permitted.\",\n      \"confidence\": 0.9\n    }\n  ],\n  \"recommendation\": \"both\"\n}",
